        "content": "<p>I noticed that we use the subscripts <code>₁</code> and <code>₂</code> for too many different things. Even more so in the write-up, where <code>⊕₁</code> denotes the 1-sum and <code>⊕₂</code> denotes the 2-sum.</p>\n<p>Perhaps we should change the notation in the {1,2,3}-sum so that <code>Mₗ</code> and <code>Mᵣ</code> are the matroids, that <code>Sₗ</code> and <code>Sᵣ</code> are their standard representations, that <code>Aₗ</code> and <code>Aᵣ</code> are the smaller matrices, that <code>Bₗ</code> and <code>Bᵣ</code> are the bigger matrices, and so on. Note that the subscripts <code>ₗ</code> and <code>ᵣ</code> don't look good in all fonts; however, JuliaMono (the font used both in my VS Code settings and in the official docgen) makes them perfectly readable.</p>\n<p>Should we change it?</p>",
